{
  "stem": "1917.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 322.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she married a guy in the synagogue, which the Romanian government did not recognize.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "His name was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Hirsch, ?] not Hersh-- [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Hirsch. ?] And he lost the wife and daughter-- two daughter in the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But actually, what happened with my uncle, he was a pharmacist.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in 1948, shortly after we applied for a visa, he disappeared.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One day as the secret police came, they picked up my uncle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we didn't know where he was, if he was alive or dead.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We didn't know what happened to him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My aunt applied for a visa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The Romanians wanted to give her a visa.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The Israelis didn't want to give her an entry visa.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The Romanians didn't want to give us an exit visa.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The Israelis wanted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Everybody wants the young people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Nobody wants the old.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "After two years, first of all, they said, well, we could go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We take our furniture, our clothing, sheets, blankets, whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I remember for about a year and a half having most of the furniture packed up in huge boxes ready to go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You could just open the box and get ready to go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was a stupid scale on the kitchen table that we would weigh every clothing item, because there was only so many kilograms you could take.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Then the order came that you could take only 15 kilogram above, which means the furniture couldn't go anymore.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When we finally got our visa, my uncle was released only to join  us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We were only-- we could take only what we could wear.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We got on the ship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we sailed for Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "When the ship was far enough from the Romanian border, my uncle said to us, I was put in jail.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
